You just have to see them again.

2214
02:03:03,109 --> 02:03:04,667
Mr. President.

2215
02:03:05,111 --> 02:03:06,442
Will the senator yield
for a question?

2216
02:03:07,179 --> 02:03:08,942
Will Senator Smith yield
to his colleague?

2217
02:03:09,415 --> 02:03:11,406
Yes, I yield for a question.

2218
02:03:11,617 --> 02:03:15,144
The senator has said he is speaking
to the people of his state.

2219
02:03:15,354 --> 02:03:18,346
He has been waiting,
as he so fancifully puts it...

2220
02:03:18,557 --> 02:03:20,991
...for them to come
marching here in droves.

2221
02:03:21,260 --> 02:03:24,320
Would the gentlemen be interested
in what those people have to say?

2222
02:03:24,530 --> 02:03:26,157
Here it comes.

2223
02:03:26,399 --> 02:03:28,094
Yes, sir, you bet I would.

2224
02:03:29,602 --> 02:03:30,569
Mr. President.

2225
02:03:30,770 --> 02:03:32,431
Have I permission to bring in...

2226
02:03:32,638 --> 02:03:34,629
...evidence of
the response of my state?

2227
02:03:34,840 --> 02:03:36,671
Is there objection?

2228
02:03:37,877 --> 02:03:38,969
You may proceed, senator.

2229
02:03:39,178 --> 02:03:40,543
Pageboys!

2230
02:04:16,048 --> 02:04:19,643
I can't stand it. I can't stand
to see him hurt like this.

2231
02:04:19,852 --> 02:04:21,285
Public opinion made to order.

2232
02:04:21,487 --> 02:04:23,011
Taylor-made.

2233
02:04:23,456 --> 02:04:27,017
There it is.
There's the gentleman's answer.

2234
02:04:27,226 --> 02:04:29,717
Telegrams. 50,000 of them...

2235
02:04:29,929 --> 02:04:31,487
...demanding that he yield this floor.

2236
02:04:31,697 --> 02:04:33,221
I invite the Senate to read them.

2237
02:04:33,466 --> 02:04:35,195
I invite my colleague to read them.

2238
02:04:35,401 --> 02:04:38,063
The people's answer to
Mr. Jefferson Smith.

2239
02:05:21,981 --> 02:05:23,881
Stop, Jeff! Stop!

2240
02:06:08,928 --> 02:06:12,420
I guess this is just another
lost cause, Mr. Paine.

2241
02:06:17,636 --> 02:06:20,935
All you people don't know
about lost causes.

2242
02:06:21,540 --> 02:06:23,098
Mr. Paine does.

2243
02:06:25,244 --> 02:06:28,771
He said once they were
the only causes worth fighting for.

2244
02:06:29,281 --> 02:06:31,340
He fought for them once.

2245
02:06:31,850 --> 02:06:35,445
For the only reason that any man
ever fights for them.

2246
02:06:38,691 --> 02:06:42,092
Because of just one plain, simple rule:

2247
02:06:42,928 --> 02:06:44,122
Love thy neighbor.

2248
02:06:45,898 --> 02:06:47,092
In this world today...

2249
02:06:47,299 --> 02:06:48,357
...full of hatred...

2250
02:06:48,567 --> 02:06:51,468
...a man who knows that one rule
has a great trust.

2251
02:06:51,670 --> 02:06:54,298
You know that rule, Mr. Paine.

2252
02:06:54,873 --> 02:06:58,001
And I loved you for it,
just as my father did.

2253
02:06:58,243 --> 02:07:01,679
And you know you fight for lost causes
harder than for any others.

2254
02:07:02,214 --> 02:07:04,444
Yes, you even die for them.

2255
02:07:06,218 --> 02:07:08,812
Like a man we both knew, Mr. Paine.

2256
02:07:12,091 --> 02:07:13,888
You think I'm licked.

2257
02:07:16,128 --> 02:07:17,493
You all think I'm licked!

2258
02:07:19,431 --> 02:07:21,365
Well, I'm not licked!

2259
02:07:21,567 --> 02:07:24,627
I'm going to stay right here
and fight for this lost cause!

2260
02:07:24,837 --> 02:07:28,432
Even if this room gets
filled with lies like these...

2261
02:07:29,274 --> 02:07:33,734
...and the Taylors and all their armies
come marching into this place.

2262
02:07:34,880 --> 02:07:37,075
Somebody will listen to me.

2263
02:08:00,606 --> 02:08:02,574
He's okay. He just fainted.

2264
02:08:14,953 --> 02:08:16,580
-Let me go!
What's the matter, Joe?

2265
02:08:16,789 --> 02:08:19,053
I'm not fit to be a senator!
I'm not fit to live!

2266
02:08:19,258 --> 02:08:20,691
Expel me!

2267
02:08:20,893 --> 02:08:22,019
Expel me, not him!

2268
02:08:22,227 --> 02:08:23,353
Willy Taylor's a fraud!

2269
02:08:23,562 --> 02:08:25,587
It's a crime against
the people who sent me here...

2270
02:08:25,798 --> 02:08:28,392
...and I committed it! Every word
that boy said is the truth!

2271
02:08:28,600 --> 02:08:30,659
Every word about Taylor
and me and graft...

2272
02:08:30,869 --> 02:08:33,133
...and the rotten political
corruption in my state!

2273
02:08:33,338 --> 02:08:35,863
Every word of it is true!
I'm not fit for office!

2274
02:08:36,075 --> 02:08:38,009
I'm not fit for
any place of honor or trust!

2275
02:08:38,210 --> 02:08:39,973
Expel me, not that boy!

2276
02:08:49,288 --> 02:08:51,119
We did it! We did it!

2277
02:08:55,728 --> 02:08:57,821
Order gentlemen! Please!

2278
02:09:07,606 --> 02:09:08,595
He did it!

2279
02:09:08,807 --> 02:09:10,502
Let go of me!

2280
02:09:14,279 --> 02:09:15,906
Yippee!